A gamified debugger extension for VS Code 
This extension includes features like:
•	Tracking debugging progress
•	Awarding achievements or points
•	Encouraging users through gamification (levels, badges, missions)
•	Interfacing with VS Code debugging API
•	Possibly storing user progress or history
Proposed Classes
1. GamifiedDebuggerExtension
•	The main controller of the extension.
•	Attributes:
          name: string
          version: string
          userProfile: UserProfile
•	Methods:
          activate()
          deactivate()
          onDebugSessionStart()
          onDebugSessionEnd()
2. UserProfile
•	Tracks user’s stats and progression.

•	Attributes:
          username: string
          level: int
          experiencePoints: int
          achievements: List<Achievement>
•	Methods:
         addExperience(points: int)
         addAchievement(achievement: Achievement)
         getProgress(): float
3. Achievement
•	Represents a badge or milestone.
•	Attributes:
          title: string
          description: string
          dateEarned: Date
•	Methods:
          display()
4. Mission
•	Represents a challenge or task (e.g., “Fix 5 breakpoints”).
•	Attributes:
         missionName: string
         goalType: string (e.g., breakpoints, step-throughs)
         targetCount: int
          currentCount: int
          isCompleted: bool
•	Methods:
         updateProgress()
         checkCompletion(): bool
5. DebuggerEventTracker
•	Hooks into VS Code debugging events.
•	Attributes:
o	debugSession: DebugSession
•	Methods:
o	trackEvents()
o	notifyUserProfile()
o	logEvent(event: DebugEvent)
Notes:
•	GamifiedDebuggerExtension uses DebuggerEventTracker, owns a UserProfile
•	UserProfile has a list of Achievement and a list of Mission
•	DebuggerEventTracker sends updates to UserProfile

